What is Classical Mereology? 
Paul Hovda

1.1.1 Schematic Type-1 Fusion
Fu1(t,[x|φ(x)]) abbreviates ∀y(y◦t↔∃x(φ(x)∧y◦x))
abbreviates
Fu1(a, [x | ∃z(Cat(z) ∧ Loves(x, z))])
∀y(y ◦ a ↔ ∃x(∃z(Cat(z) ∧ Loves(x, z)) ∧ y ◦ x))

1.1.2 Type-2 Fusion
Fu2(t, [x | φ(x)])

1.2.1 Set-theoretic Type-2 Fusion
Fu2(t, s) abbreviates
∀x(x ∈ s → x ≤ t) ∧ ∀y(y ≤ t → ∃x(x ∈ s ∧ y ◦ x))

1.3.1 Min Upper Bound
Mub(t,φx) abbreviates
∀x(φx →x≤t)∧∀w(∀x(φx →x≤w)→t≤w)
